<DocsLayout title="Requirements" description="Meet the client, understand the brief, and write the PRD yourself.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Requirements</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">In Projects 1 and 2, the PRD was written for you. Now you write it. You'll meet the client, understand what they need, and turn that into a structured requirements document that AI can implement and you can verify.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Templates are available at <a href="/templates">/templates</a>.</strong> You'll paste the client brief into Claude (the chat interface, not Claude Code) along with the PRD template and a prompt. Then you review what Claude generates — checking for scope creep, missing requirements, and vague acceptance criteria.</p>
  </Callout>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Work through these in order:</p>

  <div class="grid gap-4">
    <Card title="1. The client brief" subtitle="Meet Sarah and understand what Clay & Co needs" href="/web-dev/projects/3/requirements/client-brief" />
    <Card title="2. Writing the PRD" subtitle="Use the prompt and template to create your requirements document" href="/web-dev/projects/3/requirements/writing-the-prd" />
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
